            <title dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07ce"><![CDATA[Principles]]></title>
            <components>
                <row>
                    <column col-sm="6">
                        <component type="text">
                            <p dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07cf"><![CDATA[The principles of green software are a core set of competencies needed to define, build and run sustainable software applications.]]></p>
                        </component>
                    </column>
                    <column col-sm="6">
                        <component type="image" src="module_02/meaning_triangle_top.png">
                            <alt dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d0"><![CDATA[]]></alt>
                        </component>
                    </column>
                </row>
            </components>
        </modal>
        <modal>
            <title dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d1"><![CDATA[Patterns]]></title>
            <components>
                <row>
                    <column col-sm="6">
                        <component type="text">
                            <p dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d2"><![CDATA[A specific example of how to apply one or more principles in a real-world example. Whereas principles describe the theory that underpins green software, patterns are the practical advice software engineers can use in their software applications today. ]]></p>
                            <p dbid="6596c74102dd2cb62b72ac50"><![CDATA[This learning will not explore patterns in detail, we aim to provide an overview of the theories of green software engineering. <strong><a target="_blank" href="https://patterns.greensoftware.foundation">Click here</a></strong>, to find out more and see examples of patterns.]]></p>
                        </component>
                    </column>
                    <column col-sm="6">
                        <component type="image" src="module_02/meaning_triangle_middle.png">
                            <alt dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d4"><![CDATA[]]></alt>
                        </component>
                    </column>
                    <column col-sm="12">
                        <component type="text">
                            <p dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d3"><![CDATA[Patterns are vendor-neutral, which means they are flexible and can be implemented in many processes, across different industries.]]></p>
                        </component>
                    </column>
                </row>
            </components>
        </modal>
        <modal>
            <title dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d5"><![CDATA[Practices]]></title>
            <components>
                <row>
                    <column col-sm="12">
                        <component type="text">
                            <p dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d6"><![CDATA[A pattern applied to a specific vendor's product, and informs engineers about how to use that product in a more sustainable way.]]></p>
                        </component>
                    </column>
                    <column col-sm="6">
                        <component type="text">
                            <p dbid="657ae1eba789759594df07d7"><![CDATA[Unlike patterns, practices are vendor-specific, which means this is how a team will utilise a pattern in a specific way.<br><br> For example, a pattern can be applied to a specific vendor's product, and informs engineers about how to use that product in a more sustainable way.]]></p>
                        </component>
                    </column>
                    <column col-sm="6">
